msgid ""
"Can be declared at the **global** level in *test modules* to apply one or "
"more :ref:`marks <marks ref>` to all test functions and methods. Can be "
"either a single mark or a list of marks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:950
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"pytestmark = pytest.mark.webtest"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:957
msgid ""
"import pytest\n"
"\n"
"pytestmark = [pytest.mark.integration, pytest.mark.slow]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:964
msgid "PYTEST_DONT_REWRITE (module docstring)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:966
msgid ""
"The text ``PYTEST_DONT_REWRITE`` can be add to any **module docstring** to "
"disable :ref:`assertion rewriting <assert introspection>` for that module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:971
msgid "Environment Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:973
msgid "Environment variables that can be used to change pytest's behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:976
msgid "PYTEST_ADDOPTS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:978
msgid ""
"This contains a command-line (parsed by the py:mod:`shlex` module) that will "
"be **prepended** to the command line given by the user, see :ref:`adding "
"default options` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:982
msgid "PYTEST_DEBUG"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:984
msgid "When set, pytest will print tracing and debug information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:987
msgid "PYTEST_PLUGINS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:989
msgid ""
"Contains comma-separated list of modules that should be loaded as plugins:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:991
msgid "export PYTEST_PLUGINS=mymodule.plugin,xdist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:996
msgid "PYTEST_DISABLE_PLUGIN_AUTOLOAD"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:998
msgid ""
"When set, disables plugin auto-loading through setuptools entrypoints. Only "
"explicitly specified plugins will be loaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1002
msgid "PYTEST_CURRENT_TEST"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1004
msgid ""
"This is not meant to be set by users, but is set by pytest internally with "
"the name of the current test so other processes can inspect it, see :ref:"
"`pytest current test env` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1008
msgid "Exceptions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1011
msgid "UsageError"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/config/exceptions.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.config.exceptions.UsageError:1
msgid "error in pytest usage or invocation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1019
msgid "Configuration Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1021
msgid ""
"Here is a list of builtin configuration options that may be written in a "
"``pytest.ini``, ``tox.ini`` or ``setup.cfg`` file, usually located at the "
"root of your repository. All options must be under a ``[pytest]`` section "
"(``[tool:pytest]`` for ``setup.cfg`` files)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1026
msgid ""
"Usage of ``setup.cfg`` is not recommended unless for very simple use cases. "
"``.cfg`` files use a different parser than ``pytest.ini`` and ``tox.ini`` "
"which might cause hard to track down problems. When possible, it is "
"recommended to use the latter files to hold your pytest configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1031
msgid ""
"Configuration file options may be overwritten in the command-line by using "
"``-o/--override``, which can also be passed multiple times. The expected "
"format is ``name=value``. For example::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1034
msgid "pytest -o console_output_style=classic -o cache_dir=/tmp/mycache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1039
msgid ""
"Add the specified ``OPTS`` to the set of command line arguments as if they "
"had been specified by the user. Example: if you have this ini file content:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1042
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --maxfail=2 -rf  # exit after 2 failures, report fail info"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1048
msgid "issuing ``pytest test_hello.py`` actually means:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1050
msgid "pytest --maxfail=2 -rf test_hello.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1054
msgid "Default is to add no options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1061
msgid ""
"Sets a directory where stores content of cache plugin. Default directory is "
"``.pytest_cache`` which is created in :ref:`rootdir <rootdir>`. Directory "
"may be relative or absolute path. If setting relative path, then directory "
"is created relative to :ref:`rootdir <rootdir>`. Additionally path may "
"contain environment variables, that will be expanded. For more information "
"about cache plugin please refer to :ref:`cache_provider`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1071
msgid ""
"Sets a directory where search upwards for ``conftest.py`` files stops. By "
"default, pytest will stop searching for ``conftest.py`` files upwards from "
"``pytest.ini``/``tox.ini``/``setup.cfg`` of the project if any, or up to the "
"file-system root."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1081
msgid "Sets the console output style while running tests:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1083
msgid "``classic``: classic pytest output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1084
msgid ""
"``progress``: like classic pytest output, but with a progress indicator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1085
msgid ""
"``count``: like progress, but shows progress as the number of tests "
"completed instead of a percent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1087
msgid ""
"The default is ``progress``, but you can fallback to ``classic`` if you "
"prefer or the new mode is causing unexpected problems:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1090
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"console_output_style = classic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1101
msgid ""
"Default encoding to use to decode text files with docstrings. :doc:`See how "
"pytest handles doctests <doctest>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1107
msgid ""
"One or more doctest flag names from the standard ``doctest`` module. :doc:"
"`See how pytest handles doctests <doctest>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1115
msgid "Allows to pick the action for empty parametersets in parameterization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1117
msgid "``skip`` skips tests with an empty parameterset (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1118
msgid "``xfail`` marks tests with an empty parameterset as xfail(run=False)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1119
msgid ""
"``fail_at_collect`` raises an exception if parametrize collects an empty "
"parameter set"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1121
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"empty_parameter_set_mark = xfail"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1129
msgid ""
"The default value of this option is planned to change to ``xfail`` in future "
"releases as this is considered less error prone, see `#3155 <https://github."
"com/pytest-dev/pytest/issues/3155>`_ for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1136
msgid ""
"Dumps the tracebacks of all threads if a test takes longer than ``X`` "
"seconds to run (including fixture setup and teardown). Implemented using the "
"`faulthandler.dump_traceback_later`_ function, so all caveats there apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1140
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"faulthandler_timeout=5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1146
msgid "For more information please refer to :ref:`faulthandler`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1155
msgid ""
"Sets a list of filters and actions that should be taken for matched "
"warnings. By default all warnings emitted during the test session will be "
"displayed in a summary at the end of the test session."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1159
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"filterwarnings =\n"
"    error\n"
"    ignore::DeprecationWarning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1167
msgid ""
"This tells pytest to ignore deprecation warnings and turn all other warnings "
"into errors. For more information please refer to :ref:`warnings`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1175
msgid "Configures how durations are recorded into the JUnit XML report:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1177
msgid ""
"``total`` (the default): duration times reported include setup, call, and "
"teardown times."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1178
msgid ""
"``call``: duration times reported include only call times, excluding setup "
"and teardown."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1180
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_duration_report = call"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1190
msgid ""
"Configures the format of the generated JUnit XML file. The possible options "
"are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1192
msgid ""
"``xunit1`` (or ``legacy``): produces old style output, compatible with the "
"xunit 1.0 format. **This is the default**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1194
msgid ""
"``xunit2``: produces `xunit 2.0 style output <https://github.com/jenkinsci/"
"xunit-plugin/blob/xunit-2.3.2/src/main/resources/org/jenkinsci/plugins/xunit/"
"types/model/xsd/junit-10.xsd>`__,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1194
msgid "which should be more compatible with latest Jenkins versions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1196
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_family = xunit2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1205
msgid "``log``, ``all``, ``out-err`` options added."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1208
msgid ""
"Configures if captured output should be written to the JUnit XML file. Valid "
"values are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1210
msgid "``log``: write only ``logging`` captured output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1211
msgid "``system-out``: write captured ``stdout`` contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1212
msgid "``system-err``: write captured ``stderr`` contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1213
msgid "``out-err``: write both captured ``stdout`` and ``stderr`` contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1214
msgid ""
"``all``: write captured ``logging``, ``stdout`` and ``stderr`` contents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1215
msgid "``no`` (the default): no captured output is written."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1217
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_logging = system-out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1227
msgid ""
"If ``junit_logging != \"no\"``, configures if the captured output should be "
"written to the JUnit XML file for **passing** tests. Default is ``True``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1230
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_log_passing_tests = False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1238
msgid ""
"To set the name of the root test suite xml item, you can configure the "
"``junit_suite_name`` option in your config file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1240
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"junit_suite_name = my_suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1247
msgid "Allow selective auto-indentation of multiline log messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1249
msgid ""
"Supports command line option ``--log-auto-indent [value]`` and config option "
"``log_auto_indent = [value]`` to set the auto-indentation behavior for all "
"logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1256
msgid "``[value]`` can be:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1254
msgid "True or \"On\" - Dynamically auto-indent multiline log messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1255
msgid ""
"False or \"Off\" or 0 - Do not auto-indent multiline log messages (the "
"default behavior)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1256
msgid ""
"[positive integer] - auto-indent multiline log messages by [value] spaces"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1258
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_auto_indent = False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1263
msgid ""
"Supports passing kwarg ``extra={\"auto_indent\": [value]}`` to calls to "
"``logging.log()`` to specify auto-indentation behavior for a specific entry "
"in the log. ``extra`` kwarg overrides the value specified on the command "
"line or in the config."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1270
msgid ""
"Enable log display during test run (also known as :ref:`\"live logging\" "
"<live_logs>`). The default is ``False``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1273
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_cli = True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1282
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:func:`time.strftime`-compatible string that will be used when "
"formatting dates for live logging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1284
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_cli_date_format = %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1289 ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1302
#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1317
msgid "For more information, see :ref:`live_logs`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1295
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:mod:`logging`-compatible string used to format live logging "
"messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1297
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_cli_format = %(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(message)s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1309
msgid ""
"Sets the minimum log message level that should be captured for live logging. "
"The integer value or the names of the levels can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1312
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_cli_level = INFO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1324
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:func:`time.strftime`-compatible string that will be used when "
"formatting dates for logging capture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1326
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_date_format = %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1331 ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1346
#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1360 ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1373
#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1387 ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1401
#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1416 ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1430
msgid "For more information, see :ref:`logging`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1338
msgid ""
"Sets a file name relative to the ``pytest.ini`` file where log messages "
"should be written to, in addition to the other logging facilities that are "
"active."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1341
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_file = logs/pytest-logs.txt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1353
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:func:`time.strftime`-compatible string that will be used when "
"formatting dates for the logging file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1355
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_file_date_format = %Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1366
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:mod:`logging`-compatible string used to format logging messages "
"redirected to the logging file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1368
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_file_format = %(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(message)s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1379
msgid ""
"Sets the minimum log message level that should be captured for the logging "
"file. The integer value or the names of the levels can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1382
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_file_level = INFO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1394
msgid ""
"Sets a :py:mod:`logging`-compatible string used to format captured logging "
"messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1396
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_format = %(asctime)s %(levelname)s %(message)s"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1408
msgid ""
"Sets the minimum log message level that should be captured for logging "
"capture. The integer value or the names of the levels can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1411
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_level = INFO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1423
msgid ""
"If set to ``False``, will disable displaying captured logging messages for "
"failed tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1425
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"log_print = False"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1435
msgid ""
"When the ``--strict-markers`` or ``--strict`` command-line arguments are "
"used, only known markers - defined in code by core pytest or some plugin - "
"are allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1438
msgid ""
"You can list additional markers in this setting to add them to the "
"whitelist, in which case you probably want to add ``--strict-markers`` to "
"``addopts`` to avoid future regressions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1442
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = --strict-markers\n"
"markers =\n"
"    slow\n"
"    serial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1452
msgid "Specifies a minimal pytest version required for running tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1454
msgid ""
"# content of pytest.ini\n"
"[pytest]\n"
"minversion = 3.0  # will fail if we run with pytest-2.8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1463
msgid ""
"Set the directory basename patterns to avoid when recursing for test "
"discovery.  The individual (fnmatch-style) patterns are applied to the "
"basename of a directory to decide if to recurse into it. Pattern matching "
"characters::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1468
msgid ""
"*       matches everything\n"
"?       matches any single character\n"
"[seq]   matches any character in seq\n"
"[!seq]  matches any char not in seq"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1473
msgid ""
"Default patterns are ``'.*', 'build', 'dist', 'CVS', '_darcs', '{arch}', '*."
"egg', 'venv'``. Setting a ``norecursedirs`` replaces the default.  Here is "
"an example of how to avoid certain directories:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1477
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"norecursedirs = .svn _build tmp*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1482
msgid ""
"This would tell ``pytest`` to not look into typical subversion or sphinx-"
"build directories or into any ``tmp`` prefixed directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1485
msgid ""
"Additionally, ``pytest`` will attempt to intelligently identify and ignore a "
"virtualenv by the presence of an activation script.  Any directory deemed to "
"be the root of a virtual environment will not be considered during test "
"collection unless ``‑‑collect‑in‑virtualenv`` is given.  Note also that "
"``norecursedirs`` takes precedence over ``‑‑collect‑in‑virtualenv``; e.g. if "
"you intend to run tests in a virtualenv with a base directory that matches "
"``'.*'`` you *must* override ``norecursedirs`` in addition to using the "
"``‑‑collect‑in‑virtualenv`` flag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1497
msgid ""
"One or more name prefixes or glob-style patterns determining which classes "
"are considered for test collection. Search for multiple glob patterns by "
"adding a space between patterns. By default, pytest will consider any class "
"prefixed with ``Test`` as a test collection.  Here is an example of how to "
"collect tests from classes that end in ``Suite``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1503
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"python_classes = *Suite"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1508
msgid ""
"Note that ``unittest.TestCase`` derived classes are always collected "
"regardless of this option, as ``unittest``'s own collection framework is "
"used to collect those tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1515
msgid ""
"One or more Glob-style file patterns determining which python files are "
"considered as test modules. Search for multiple glob patterns by adding a "
"space between patterns:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1519
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"python_files = test_*.py check_*.py example_*.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1524
msgid "Or one per line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1526
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"python_files =\n"
"    test_*.py\n"
"    check_*.py\n"
"    example_*.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1534
msgid ""
"By default, files matching ``test_*.py`` and ``*_test.py`` will be "
"considered test modules."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1540
msgid ""
"One or more name prefixes or glob-patterns determining which test functions "
"and methods are considered tests. Search for multiple glob patterns by "
"adding a space between patterns. By default, pytest will consider any "
"function prefixed with ``test`` as a test.  Here is an example of how to "
"collect test functions and methods that end in ``_test``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1546
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"python_functions = *_test"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1551
msgid ""
"Note that this has no effect on methods that live on a ``unittest ."
"TestCase`` derived class, as ``unittest``'s own collection framework is used "
"to collect those tests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1555
msgid "See :ref:`change naming conventions` for more detailed examples."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1562
msgid ""
"Sets list of directories that should be searched for tests when no specific "
"directories, files or test ids are given in the command line when executing "
"pytest from the :ref:`rootdir <rootdir>` directory. Useful when all project "
"tests are in a known location to speed up test collection and to avoid "
"picking up undesired tests by accident."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1568
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"testpaths = testing doc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1573
msgid ""
"This tells pytest to only look for tests in ``testing`` and ``doc`` "
"directories when executing from the root directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1579
msgid ""
"List of fixtures that will be applied to all test functions; this is "
"semantically the same to apply the ``@pytest.mark.usefixtures`` marker to "
"all test functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1583
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"usefixtures =\n"
"    clean_db"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1592
msgid ""
"If set to ``True``, tests marked with ``@pytest.mark.xfail`` that actually "
"succeed will by default fail the test suite. For more information, see :ref:"
"`xfail strict tutorial`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/reference.rst:1597
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"xfail_strict = True"
msgstr ""
